{
  "texts": [
    "3) Interfacility communication: Effective communication between the primary and comprehensive stroke centers is crucial for seamless transfer and continuity of care (Patterson, 2023).",
    "Delays may arise from communication barriers or breakdowns in information exchange between healthcare providers (Patterson, 2023).",
    "4) Bed availability: Limited beds or resources at the comprehensive stroke center may lead to delays in accepting transferred patients.",
    "Capacity constraints can exacerbate delays, particularly during peak demand periods (Monks, 2016).",
    "Transferring the patient to the accepting facility's emergency room helps mitigate this issue, as the patient does not require a traditional hospital bed but can proceed directly to the angiography suite."
  ]
}